==English==

===Etymology===
From the color of dress shirts worn by professional and clerical workers, as opposed to the rugged denim and chambray shirts normally worn by manual workers.

===Adjective===
'''white-collar'''

#Engaged or trained in working in an office, as opposed to manual work.  Professional or clerical class.
#: ''White-collar workers represent an augmenting segment of society.''
#Of or relating to persons who work in an office, as opposed to [[blue-collar]].  
#: ''White-collar value can keep marriages together.''
#Pertaining to the culture of white-collar workers.

